## Key reuse

- `schema_builder.build_schema_md()` (`backend/agent/schema_builder.py:194`) — called unchanged by `complete_setup()`
- `schema_builder.discover_entity_types()` (line 122) — used unchanged for post-setup operation
- `schema_builder.bootstrap_type_yamls()` (line 98) — still safe; it only writes if folder exists and has no `_type.yaml`; wizard creates both together so no collision
- `WikiManager._init_llm()` (`backend/agent/wiki_manager.py:214`) — the LLM factory logic (reads `AI_PROVIDER`, `AI_MODEL`, env keys) is extracted or duplicated into `setup_wizard.py` so the suggest-schema endpoint can build an LLM without needing a full WikiManager instance. Alternatively, make `_init_llm` a standalone function imported by both.
- `PydanticOutputParser` (LangChain, already in `requirements.txt`) — used to parse the LLM's JSON response for `SuggestedSchema`

